'''''Star Wars Insider'' 78''' is the seventy-eighth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[October 5]], [[2004]]. This issue came packaged with promotional card P1 from the [[Topps]] trading card set ''[[2004 Topps Star Wars Heritage]]''.

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"[[Comlink (department)|Comlink]]"
*"[[Skywalking]]: News from Around the Galaxy"
*"[[Jedi Library (department)|Jedi Library]]" &mdash; Where's Wuher? {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Drawn by the Force]]" &mdash; The Royal Sampler {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace|Dan Wallace]]}}
*"[[Set Piece|Technical Readout]]" &mdash; Jawa Sandcrawler {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]]}}
*"[[Star Wars Q&A|Ask the Master]]" {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Jabba's Collection]]" {{C|by starwars.hasbro.com}}
*"[[Anchorhead Arcade]]" &mdash; ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]'' {{C|by [[Justin Lambros]]}}
*"[[Best of Hyperspace]]" &mdash; He's Big, and He's Back: Chewbacca Returns {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Bonnie Burton]]}}
*[[Bantha Tracks (department)|''Bantha Tracks'']] Vol. 9
*"[[Laugh It Up, Fuzzball]]" {{C|by ''Insider'' Staff}}

===Features===
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*:<small>In late [[August]] and early [[September]], [[Lucasfilm]] revisited the historic Shepperton Studios in England for its first round of pick-up shoots.</small>
*"[[50 Factoids About the Original Star Wars Trilogy|50 Factoids About the Original ''Star Wars'' Trilogy]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>To celebrate the release of the Star Wars trilogy on DVD, ''Insider'' has gone to great lengths to unearth 50 factoids about the historic films. Use what you learn wisely.</small>
*"[[The Making of the Star Wars Trilogy DVDs: Restoring the Galaxy|The Making of the ''Star Wars'' Trilogy DVDs: Restoring the Galaxy]]" {{C|by ''Insider'' Staff}}
*:<small>Before the films could be brought home on DVD, they had to go through quite a makeover&mdash;and it wasn't easy.</small>
*"[[Star Wars Battlefront: See the Movies, Live the Battles|''Star Wars'' Battlefront: See the Movies, Live the Battles]]" {{C|by [[Justin Lambros]]}}
*:<small>''Insider'' talks with Pandemic Executive Producer [[Greg Borrud]] to get the details on the exclusive [[Star Wars: Battlefront|demo]] available with the DVDs.</small>
*"[[The Menus of the Star Wars Trilogy DVDs: Navigating the Galaxy|The Menus of the ''Star Wars'' Trilogy DVDs: Navigating the Galaxy]]" {{C|by [[Brett Rector]]}}
*:<small>''Insider'' interviews Van Ling to gain insight into the process of creating the DVD menus. Plus, we tell you what's in the boxed set.</small>
*"[[The Artist Strikes Back: An Interview with Ralph McQuarrie]]" {{C|by [[Ron Magid]]}}
*:<small>In the second part of our three-part interview, [[Ralph McQuarrie]] speaks to Ron Magid about bringing [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']] to visual life.</small>
*"[[A Subject of the Divine]]" {{C|by [[Abel G. Peña|Abel Peña]]}}
*:<small>Before there was ''Star Wars'' or even ''American Graffiti'', there was [[Wikipedia:THX 1138|''THX 1138'']]. ''Insider'' explores [[George Lucas]]' monumental first film just as it comes home on DVD.</small>

